{"sequence":17,"timestamp":"2026-04-12T15:41:49.446017814Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-fc2e6e6b","body":"In `src/adapters/worktree.rs:48-70` and `src/adapters/worktree.rs:138-140`, stop pinning `WorktreeAdapter` to the first hard-coded absolute git path before consulting `PATH`. On Linux/macOS this will usually select `/usr/bin/git`, which means any `PATH`-injected wrapper is silently ignored for every worktree operation. That is a correctness regression: the existing hard-rollback failure scenario in `src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs:5894-5928` now no longer intercepts `git reset --hard`, and `target/debug/ralph-burning conformance run --filter SC-ROLLBACK-008` fails with `expected failure, got success`. Preserve ambient `PATH` resolution (or search `PATH` first with executable checks) so fake/custom git binaries still work.","dedup_key":"94d810b7cd6940d2784dc190c8ba9481a7dbf22568c108cafacbe9fe7cd52f42","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260412152311","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
